On Sep 20, 2016 at 12:16 AM, <Kedzier3> wrote:

Hey classmates, my name is August and I have a question for all my fellow students participating in discussion for physics 122. I'm curious as to how your discussions are operating. Today, our in-class, non-graded discussion homework was handed out by our TA after our quiz. After it was handed out, we did not finish a single question. All our TA did was write a few formulas on the board and then walk around for about 30mins. In fact, when asked to finish a problem to help a student the TA stated that he wouldn't because "the TA already knew how to finish it and if the student had a problem with that he should see the TA after class." I would like to know know if you guys are going through and finishing questions fully or if your all just being left to do problems on your own without much help. Please get back to me with any input you have as this is affecting many students in our class and I would like to know if switching discussions would help in anyway or If we're better off setting up our own study groups. Please don't be shy and include your discussion section.

Thanks so much, hope you guys all get A's

-August```
